properties.areaDesc: San Juan County; Admiralty Inlet Area
properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued January 23 at 2:26PM PST until January 24 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Minor coastal flooding expected.

* WHERE...San Juan County and Admiralty Inlet Area.

* WHEN...From 1 AM to 7 AM PST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Flooding of lots, parks, and roads with only
isolated road closures expected.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The combination of high astronomical tide,
breezy winds, and low pressure will result in minor tidal
overflow at Port Townsend and Friday Harbor. High tide at Port
Townsend is around 530 AM PST at 9.5 feet and high tide at
Friday Harbor is around 630 AM PST at 8.8 feet. The tidal
anomaly is around 1 foot.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 1 AM TO 7 AM PST FRIDAY
